    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Development in Hewlett Neck largely dates from before the 1960s, giving the village a historic, early‑midcentury feel.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://hewlettneckhempsteadneighborhood.org/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The village’s Mallow Reach Bridge, maintained by the town, spans the Auerbach Canal and is a notable local landmark.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        26
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hewlett_Harbor%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The nearest Long Island Rail Road stop is Hewlett station on the Far Rockaway Branch, just a short drive from the village.",
